ssmtp (2.65-0ppa1) unstable; urgency=low

  Merged Debian patches into mainline source
  Added option to be able to compile against openssl instead of gnutls

  Releasing this version so ssmtp can work with Amazon's SES better as
  recent Amazon changes have made email sending unreliable.  Switching
  SSL libraries to OpenSSL seems to fix things.  I don't know how gnutls's
  version differs when it talks to Amazon, nor am I able to really figure
  out why without more help from their side.

 -- Tyler Akins <fidian@rumkin.com>  Fri, 04 Oct 2013 19:48:03 +0500

